  "name": "Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus (Comprehensive)",
  "description": "Comprehensive test case covering all 5 paths of the Northwestern University T2DM algorithm. This evaluates the LLM's overall approach to identifying T2DM patients. The algorithm identifies cases through diagnosis codes, medications, and abnormal lab values. Path 4 patients have NO diagnosis code - only medications and abnormal labs. See path-specific test cases (phekb-type-2-diabetes-dx, -meds, -labs) for targeted evaluation.",
  "prompt": "Find all patients who may have type 2 diabetes mellitus. Consider patients who have a formal diabetes diagnosis, those prescribed diabetes medications like metformin or sulfonylureas, and those with elevated hemoglobin A1c levels at or above 6.5 percent.",
